ose-one">types of design agencies</a>, since this is where things often get confusing.</p><p>Some agencies bundle design into a<strong> full-service dev package</strong>. That sounds efficient until you realize your designer juggles five projects and works off a dev team’s spec sheet.</p><p><strong>Design-only agencies</strong> like us at Eleken work differently. We don’t code. We don’t overscope. We just do focused, product-first design, which starts in Figma and ends with something your devs can build.</p><p>Here’s what you should expect:</p><ul role="list"><li>Clickable mobile prototypes<br/><br/></li><li>Mobile-specific design systems<br/><br/></li><li>UX audits with actionable takeaways<br/><br/></li><li>Final Figma files your devs will understand</li></ul><p>Now that we understand what mobile app design agencies do and how they differ, let’s examine the companies that design apps in 2025.</p><div class="w-embed"><div class="banner-wrap banner">
